The paper discusses a self-organizing particle system, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The algorithm proposed is for movement and coordination, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses techniques from Markov chain analysis, which is a common tool in the study of distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper discusses the behavior of army ants, which is a biological inspiration for swarm robotics (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a stochastic algorithm, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
